# Copy to ".env.local" in this folder, fill in values, restart Vite.

# --- Public site availability (Vercel Production only) ---
# Serves a static maintenance page instead of the app; local dev: leave unset.
# VITE_SITE_UNAVAILABLE=1
#
# https://vite.dev/guide/env-and-mode

# --- Desktop installer (web UI only; Electron hides this) ---
# Default URL uses `git remote origin` + package.json version (same as `npm run print:desktop-download-url`).
# If origin is missing in CI, set owner/repo explicitly:
# VITE_INKWELL_GITHUB_OWNER_REPO=YourOrg/inkwell
# Full installer override (CDN, etc.):
# VITE_INKWELL_DESKTOP_DOWNLOAD_URL=https://github.com/OWNER/REPO/releases/latest/download/...
# Private repo + same-site hosting on Vercel (see docs/DESKTOP.md): production build can fetch the Release asset:
# On Vercel Production use either:
#   VITE_INKWELL_DESKTOP_DOWNLOAD_URL=/downloads/Inkwell-Setup-latest.exe
#   VITE_INKWELL_DESKTOP_DOWNLOAD_URL=https://YOUR_DOMAIN/downloads/Inkwell-Setup-latest.exe
# Local `npm run dev`: GitHub default still 404s for private repos — point at production binary:
#   VITE_INKWELL_DESKTOP_DOWNLOAD_URL=https://YOUR_DOMAIN/downloads/Inkwell-Setup-latest.exe
# Set on Vercel only (never commit): INKWELL_GITHUB_RELEASE_TOKEN=<classic PAT, repo read>
# Emergency: INKWELL_SKIP_DESKTOP_INSTALLER_FETCH=1 skips fetch so `npm run build` succeeds (download URL broken until fixed).
# Optional (Vercel preview builds — downloads ~120MB each time): INKWELL_FETCH_DESKTOP_INSTALLER_ON_PREVIEW=1
# Any other public HTTPS URL to the .exe works as an override (CDN, Storage, etc.).
# Private GitHub repo: unauthenticated /releases/latest/download/ often returns 404 — use Vercel path above or another HTTPS URL.
